Zarb JP(1), Zarb GA.

Author information:
(1)Prosthodontics, Faculty of Dentistry, University of Toronto, Toronto, 
Ontario, Canada. john.zarb@utoronto.ca

OBJECTIVE: This paper reports on the long-term outcome of patients with Kennedy 
Class IV partial edentulism treated in the Implant Prosthodontic Unit (IPU) at 
the University of Toronto, Toronto, Ontario.
METHODS: The information for this paper was gathered from the charts of the 
first 30 consecutive, partially edentulous patients treated at the IPU. These 
patients all had Class IV edentulism and formed part of the original prospective 
