patients with 86 implants supporting 31 fixed prostheses and 3 overdentures had 
been followed for an average of 12 years (range 7 16 years). The overall 
survival of implants was 92%. The difference between men (94%) and women (89%) 
was not statistically significant.
CONCLUSIONS: This report is an interim update on an ongoing long-term 
prospective study. The results so far demonstrate a high survival rate for Br 
nemark implants supporting tissue-integrated prostheses for the management of 
anterior partial edentulism.

